<DOCNO> XIE19990703.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Armed Bandits Attempt to Rob Texaco Office in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Angolan police confirmed Friday that
the fierce fighting in downtown Luanda Thursday afternoon took
place when some armed bandits attempted to rob the office of
world-renowned Texaco oil company here in the capital.
</P>
<P>
A report by Angola's criminal investigation police said six
bandits armed with AKM submachine gun planned to attack the Texaco
office in Alvalade district when they met resistance from the
security guards and police. Four of the six bandits were killed
while two others escaped.
</P>
<P>
The police were told that the bandits belong to a notorious
local gang named "Groupo Band" whose head is Joao Band. The gang
are often engaged in killings, car jacking and attacking
companies.
</P>
<P>
The protracted civil war in Angola has resulted in the
scattering of many weapons among ordinary citizens, hence constant
armed robberies.
</P>
<P>
The serious economic crisis in the country also gives rise to
increasing crimes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
