<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Troops Kill 3 Rebels on Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Iranian security forces on Friday
killed three members of the outlawed Mujahideen Khalq Organization
(MKO) who were responsible for several explosions in Iran, the
Iranian Intelligence Ministry announced.
</P>
<P>
The shoot-out took place when the MKO rebels were trying to
flee into Iraq after carrying out several explosions in Iran, the
Islamic Republic News Agency quoted the ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
Two explosions occurred Thursday night in two cities in western
Iran, causing minor damages. No casualties were reported.
</P>
<P>
The first explosion occurred in Kermanshah, capital of the
western province of Kermanshah, and the other in Ahvaz, the
capital of the southwestern border province of Khuzetstan.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the MKO members robbed a car and took its
driver as hostage while fleeing, but Iranian security forces
rescued the hostage.
</P>
<P>
The MKO, a military group which fought against the former
Iranian Shah regime, was outlawed in 1981 following political
differences with the ruling cleric regime and fled into Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Last month, several MKO members were killed or injured in Iraq
in a series of explosion attacks which were reportedly carried out
by Iranian forces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
