<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Calls on OAU to Bring Peace to Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles
Zenawi said Friday that the Organization of African Unity (OAU)
and the Inter- Governmental Authority on Development (IGAD) should
continue their efforts to bring peace to Somalia.
</P>
<P>
Meles made the remarks during his talks here with Layashi
Yakare, special envoy of Algerian president.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, Meles discussed with
the visiting Algerian envoy on issues related to the OAU summit
slated for July 12 in Algerian capital Algiers.
</P>
<P>
On the Ethio-Eritrean border dispute, Meles said Eritrea must
withdraw from all occupied Ethiopian territories as required by
the OAU framework agreement on peace.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian Minister of Trade and Industry Kassahun Ayele had
earlier travelled to Algeria to deliver Meles' message to the
Algerian leader. The Ethio-Eritrean crisis and the Somali issue
will be discussed at the forthcoming OAU summit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
