<HEADLINE> Pinochet Enters Clinic for Heart Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Former Chilean leader Augusto
Pinochet has been taken to a British hospital for heart tests, his
spokesman said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"He had been complaining of feeling uncomfortable all week. So
the doctor decided today that he should have some tests," the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"He went in today to a clinic to have a cardiogram," said the
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
"He may be held overnight. It depends on what they think. It
could end up being nothing," he said.
</P>
<P>
General Pinochet, 83, is under house arrest on the south-west
suburb of London, awaiting extradition proceedings to Spain to
start on September 27.
</P>
<P>
The former leader was arrested last October in a London
hospital while he was recovering from an operation. A Spanish
judge accuses him of human rights abuses during his 1973-1990
rule in Chile and wants to try him in Madrid.  
</P>
</TEXT>
