<HEADLINE> Ethiopia, Iran to Promote Commercial Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian and Iranian
chambers of commerce have signed an agreement to promote bilateral
cooperation, the Ethiopian News Agency (ENA) reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Aschalew Haile, president of the Ethiopian Chamber of Commerce,
signed the agreement during his visit to Iran from June 27 and
July 1.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the two sides will exchange information
and share experiences concerned.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Iran, Aschalew held "fruitful" discussions
with representatives of more than 100 Iranian business firms, and
visited, among others, food complexes and heavy-duty truck
assembly plants, said the report. 
</P>
