<HEADLINE> Ghali to Visit Canada for La Francophonie Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General of La Francophonie
Boutros Boutros-Ghali will visit Ottawa from July 4 to 6 for the
25 Session of the Parliamentary Assembly of La Francophonie (APF),
the Canadian government announced here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Minister for International Co-operation Diane Marlea said that
Canada will use the opportunity to advance preparations for La
Francophonie Summit scheduled for Moncton, Brunswick, this
September.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Mr. Boutros-Ghali will hold talks with Prime
Minister Jean Chretien, New Brunswick Premier Bernard Lord,
Foreign Minister Lloyd Axworthy and Minister Marleau.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Boutros-Ghali also plans to visit facilities to be used for
the sports and cultural events slated for the Francophonie games
in July 2001, according to the announcement.
</P>
<P>
The APF, the consultative assembly of La Francophonie founded
in 1967, initiates activities to promote interparliamentary
co-operation within the international francophone community.
</P>
</TEXT>
