<HEADLINE> Kouchner Named to Head U.N. Civilian Mission in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan Friday decided to appoint Bernard Kouchner, a high-ranking
French Government official, as the head of the U.N. civil
operation in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo, a U.N. spokesman
announced.
</P>
<P>
The announcement came in a statement, issued by the U.N.
spokesman, saying that "the Secretary-General has informed the
President of the Security Council of his intention to appoint Mr.
Bernard Kouchner as his Special Representative to head the United
Nations Mission in Kosovo, Federal Republic of Yugoslavia."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Annan appointed Jack Covey, who is an American, as
Principal Deputy to his Special Representative, the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
The four major components of the mission will each be headed by
a Deputy Special Representative as follows: Interim Civil
