<HEADLINE> Mozambique's 11 Oppositions to Jointly Participate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique's 11 oppositions
including the National Resistance of Mozambique (Renamo), the
largest opposition, have decided to jointly take part in the
presidential and parliamentary elections slated for late 1999.
</P>
<P>
They had chosen Afonso Dhlakama, leader of the Renamo, as their
sole presidential candidate, the Mozambique News Agency reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The oppositions include the Renovation Democratic Party, the
National Convention Party, the Liberal and Democratic Party of
Mozambique, the National Movement of Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
Maneca Daniel, spokesman for the 11 parties, said Thursday that
the alliance of the oppositions is the only best way to defeat the
ruling Mozambique Liberation Front (Frelimo).
</P>
<P>
The 11 parties will use the symbol of Renamo during the
elections. If the alliance wins in the election, said Daniel,
they will form a national unity government enveloping all
political parties. 
