Sources from the ministry said the drugs contained in 19
plastic bags were hidden in the luggage of two Angolan citizens
heading for Paris, France.
</P>
<P>
The two drug smuggling suspects were arrested on the spot,
despite their attempt to bribe Customs police with 50 U.S.
dollars. The case is under further investigation, according to
the sources.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the Angolan government reportedly burnt
more than 400 kilograms of marijuana on the World Drug Day which
falls on June 26. The large amount of drugs were captured by
police during the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Police sources in the country said drug smuggling was on the
rise in the past years. The drugs, mainly from Brazil on the
other side of the Atlantic, are destined for European countries
via Angola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
