<HEADLINE> U.S. Reassured of No Defense Ties between Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 2 (Xinhua) -- the U.S. State Department said
on Friday that it was pleased Greece refused to have any defense
cooperation with Iran.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian news agency IRNA said on Tuesday that visiting
Greek Defense Minister Akis Tsohatzopoulos told a news conference
in Tehran that Greece and Iran would "promote defense
cooperation" by signing a letter of understanding.
</P>
<P>
Washington, worried over the news, has asked its embassy to
make confirmation for that and was informed that it was an
"erroneous" report.
</P>
<P>
"We are pleased to have been informed through our embassy in
Athens that this report is erroneous and that Greece has no
intention of signing any defense agreement or establishing a
defense relationship with Iran," State Department spokesman
James Foley said. 
</P>
