<HEADLINE> China Marks International Cooperatives Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The All-China Federation of Supply
and Marketing Cooperatives today held activities in Beijing today
Marking the 77th International Cooperatives Alliance (ICA) Day.
</P>
<P>
This year's theme is "public policy and laws on cooperatives",
whose purpose is to stress cooperatives' legal status and equality
with other kinds of organizations and enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Supply and marketing cooperatives from across China have been
holding their own activities today to celebrate the event.
</P>
<P>
ICA was founded in 1895 and now has more than 230 members in
over 120 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
China's supply and marketing cooperatives are farmers'
cooperative organizations. After 40 years of development, these
national supply and marketing cooperatives have 180 million rural
family members and annual sales and purchases of more than 100
billion yuan (12.8 billion U.S. dollars). 
</P>
