<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Wins First Gold Medal in Palma Universiada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PALMA, Spain, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Russian gymnasts took the
first gold medal from the 20th Universiade here this afternoon,
finishing first in the women's gymnastic team event.
</P>
<P>
The Russian squad spearheaded by Svetlana Khorkina, the 1996
Olympic champion and 1997 world champion, collected a total of 113.
487 points, edging Ukraine to second on 112.974 points.)
</P>
<P>
Khorkina also scored the day-high 9.825 points from the uneven
bars.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese women only finished third with 111.174 points as
all three world champions Liu Xuan, Kui Yuanyuan and Bi Wenjing
are off their peaks, said Gao Jian, chef de mission of the Chinese
sports delegation.
</P>
<P>
Both Russia and Ukraine have dispatched the same squads who
have concluded the Olympic qualifiers early this month in Pusan,
South Korea where in China collected five individual gold medals
with its first-string young gymnasts.
</P>
<P>
"I am satisfied with the performances of our gymnasts here
since none of them are in the peak, and only Bi Wenjing and Shi
Jia made two glarying mistakes this afternoon," said the Chinese
official.
</P>
<P>
"But we have to find the solution to the dire fact that our
women gymnasts seldom can keep their forms in their elder ages
while their peers from other countries, mostly Russia and Ukraine,
can still attain their world-class caliber."
</P>
<P>
"Apart from the physical factor, we still have to improve our
training methods," said Gao.
</P>
<P>
He explained that the star-studded Chinese gymnastic team
actually is the second-string squad as only those aged from 18-28
are eligible for the University Games, and China can only find
those five women for the Palma gymnastics competition.
</P>
<P>
Mexico's Denisse Lopez collected the event-high 9.625 points
from the vault with the most difficult routine which boast s of a
record scoring merit of 9.9 points.
</P>
<P>
Kui Yuanyuan of China scored the second day-best of 9.750
points in the uneven bars, Elena Produnova of Russia was also
awarded the same scoring from the beam while the highest mark of 9.
600 in the floor exercise was given to another Russian Elena
Dolgopolova. 
</P>
</TEXT>
