<DOCNO> XIE19990703.0072 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Strengthens Water Resource Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Council of Ministers of
Ethiopia has approved the water resources management draft policy
deemed to advance the sustainable utilization of the water
resources of the Horn of African country.
</P>
<P>
The council in its ordinary session Friday said this national
policy would enable the country to utilize its water resources in
a sustainable and equitable manner, the state-run Ethiopian News
Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The council said there is uneven distribution of rivers with 80
percent to 90 percent of the water resource concentrating in the
northwest, west and southwest of the country where only 40 percent
of the population lives.
</P>
<P>
The eastern and central parts of Ethiopia in which only 10 to
20 percent of the river basins is found is inhabited by over 60
percent of the total population, it said.
</P>
<P>
The council said the policy would be instrumental in the
preservation of water resources and the augmentation of their
usage for improved socio- economic gains.
</P>
<P>
It said the policy creates a system for integrated and
efficient water management in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
