<HEADLINE> More Athletes Register For Universiada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PALMA, Spain, July 3 (Xinhua) -- A total of 3,962 students-
athletes from 114 countries and regions have officially registered
for the 20th University Games to be opened here late this evening.
</P>
<P>
The Palma edition, in the 50th anniversary of the founding of
the FISU, also features a string of quality competitors, the
organizing committee said.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish team counts numerous world-class athletes like high
jumpers Kasja Bergqist, Stefan Holm and Staffan Strad, and women
discus thrower Anna Soderberg.
</P>
<P>
In gymnastics, world stars also arrived in Palma such as China'
s 1997 world champion Liu Xuan, 1998 Word Cup winner Bi Wenjing
and Russian Khorkina Svetlana, the 1996 Olympic and 1997 world
champions winner.
</P>
<P>
Host Spain showed up the strong field led Alberto Portas,
ranked 84th in the ATP list. University Games reigning champion
Wang Shi-Ting of Chinese Taipei and Janet Lee who ranked 73rd and
105th respectively in the WTA list.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, the soccer tournament was kicked off with Morocco
beating Uruguay 3-0, Spain over Australia 1-0, South Korea downing
Britain 4-1.
</P>
<P>
In other games, Italy beat Japan 1-0, Mexico edged Ireland 1-0,
Iran ousted Ukraine 2-0, Czech Republic tied with Nigeria 2-2, and
South Africa failed to show up against Brazil.
</P>
<P>
However, the opening ceremony will be held in Son Moix stadium
at 2200 (local time). 
</P>
