<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Preparatory Committee Closes 9th Plenary Session (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The two-day 9th plenary session of
the Preparatory Committee for the Macao Special Administrative
Region (SAR) ended here today with a number of rulings on Macao's
return to the motherland adopted.
</P>
<P>
Members passed decisions on the work of the Macao SAR's first
chief executive before December 19 and on swearing in personnel
and adopted a specific measure for producing the Macao SAR's
judiciary.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Qian Qichen, who is chairman of the committee,
said at the closing session that the documents are important for
preparatory work of the Macao SAR and that, with the successful
selection of the first chief executive, the work for organizing
the Macao SAR has entered a practical stage.
</P>
<P>
The formation of the Macao SAR's administrative, legislative,
and judicial bodies and other matters related to establishing the
Macao SAR need to be finished before December 19, Qian said,
adding that the decision on the first chief executive's work
before December 19 has provided a legal basis for him to start
right now on forming the SAR.
</P>
<P>
He explained that the adoption of a specific measure for
choosing the Macao SAR's judiciary is another important document
of the Preparatory Committee.
</P>
<P>
The people of Macao have a good understanding and strong desire
to govern Macao in accordance with the law and pay a great deal of
attention to forming the judiciary, he said, adding that the
adopted measure reflects regulations in the Basic Law of the Macao
SAR and will surely win their support.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990703.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Preparatory Committee Closes 9th Plenary Session (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Qian said that the Macao SAR's court holds trials independently
and rejects any intervention, but the Basic Law is the SAR's
fundamental constitutional law and an accurate understanding and
implementation of it is the prerequisite of a good handling of the
Macao SAR's affairs and relations with the Central Government.
</P>
<P>
According to him, President Jiang Zemin and other Central
Government leaders have repeatedly emphasized that the Central
Government will stick to the "one country, two systems" policy and
will never meddle in the SAR's autonomous affairs.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Standing Committee of the Ninth National
People's Congress passed the Law on Stationing Troops in the Macao
SAR at its 10th session on Monday and that had a good response
from Macao residents. Stationing troops in Macao is a symbol of
China's sovereignty over Macao and an effective way for the
Central Government to control defense there and conducive to
maintaining Macao's stability, he explained.
</P>
<P>
In coming months, the Preparatory Committee will study Macao's
municipal bodies, the transition of some legislators, Macao's
existing laws, financial relations with the mainland, and
preparations for celebrating the return of Macao to the motherland,
he said.
</P>
<P>
A press release from the Preparatory Committee today said that
the Preparatory Committee's next session will be held August 28
and 29 in Beijing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
