<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Seminar on Breast Endoscopy in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- More than 50 Chinese and Japanese
specialists gathered here today at a seminar on using endoscopy to
diagnose breast cancer, the first of its kind ever held in China.
</P>
<P>
The technique involves using a super-fine optic fiber endoscope
to probe for small tumors in the breast area that cannot be found
through conventional methods.
</P>
<P>
Breast cancer has experienced a steep rise in China in recent
years and it is hoped that the new method will help identify
breast cancer at an early stage so that it can be cured in most
cases.  
</P>
