<HEADLINE> Int'l Dragon Boat Festival Set Off Held in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- A total of 27 teams of paddlers
from seven countries and regions around the world and 90 local
teams are competing in the Hong Kong Dragon Boat Festival
International Races 1999, which opened Saturday on river banks of
Shatin.
</P>
<P>
Crews from China's mainland, Canada, Japan, Italy, Macao, the
Philippines and the United States are taking part in the two-day
event organized by the Hong Kong Tourism Association (HKTA) in
conjunction with the Provisional Regional Council.
</P>
<P>
Under this year's race format, all crews in the men's races
will be ranked according to qualifying times and then divided into
three groups of 24, ensuring that every crew competes against
other crews of similar class.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the men's, the women's and the mixed international
championship, this year's race categories include the men's open,
the women's open and a range of other championship races
especially for teams representing local industries and professions.
</P>
<P>
The festival is now in its 24th year, and although it retains
much of the colorful 2,000-year-old Chinese tradition, it has
evolved into an exciting international event, attracting
spectators and competitors from all over the world.
</P>
<P>
Since its inception in 1976, the Hong Kong festival remains one
of the sport's favorite annual events, attracting paddlers from
all around the world to test their strength on the 640-meter-long
course.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the races, there are also crazy bathtub races on
Sunday afternoon and riverside entertainment in the form of "
Biergarten" featuring food and drink stalls, souvenir booths, beer-
drinking and cheerleading and live bands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
