<HEADLINE> Beijing Stopping Illegal Express Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital is dealing
harshly with the local postal express service, according to city
government officials.
</P>
<P>
There are about 180 postal express services in Beijing, but
nearly 70 have not registered with industrial and commercial
administrative departments, while some are engaged in malpractices
and have brought harm to the interests of the state and customers.
</P>
<P>
So the city adopted the country's first local express service
law with its "Administrative Regulations on Postal Express
Business Activities" to improve the local market on June 1.
</P>
<P>
Companies that are found not to qualify for the postal express
services during the clean-up campaign will not be given a license
and all such "underground" business will be outlawed.  
</P>
