<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Magma Moves Up Mayon's Crater, Says Volcanology Institute </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' seismic stations at
Mayon's slopes Saturday recorded high frequency volcanic tremors,
which showed signs of a possible eruption in days or weeks.
</P>
<P>
In a bulletin issued here, the Philippine Institute of
Volcanology and Seismology (Phivolcs) said that its stations at
Mayon's slopes continued to record high frequency volcanic tremors
representing movement of magma towards the summit of the volcano,
about 330 kilometers southeast of Manila.
</P>
<P>
"During the period from 8:00 a.m. on July 2 to 8:00 a.m. on
July 3, the network likewise detected one high frequency volcanic
earthquake," it said.
</P>
<P>
During the past 24 hours, it said, moderate levels of steaming
activity were detected and the steam was noted to be emitted
without force from the crater before being drifted by the
prevailing wind.
</P>
<P>
The Phivolcs Thursday raised Mayon's alert level from 1 to 2,
saying if "the volcanic tremor and other physical indicators
persist in the coming days, the situation at Mayon could well
likely progress towards an eruption, possibly in a few weeks time
or even less."
</P>
<P>
In its Friday bulletin, the Phivolcs also increased the danger
zone at the volcano's southeastern quadrant from six kilometers to
seven kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Mayon, however, stood rather calm in the backdrop, puffing up
white smoke carried by the wind mostly towards the southwestern
direction, residents in the area said.
</P>
<P>
The treacherous calmness of the volcano is reminiscent of the
June 22 Phreatic blast and the February 1993 eruption that killed
about 70 farmers. Both eruptions caught everyone by surprise.
</P>
<P>
Governor Al Francis Bichara of Albay province, where Mayon is
located, said all disaster task units from rescue and evacuation
to rehabilitation have been well briefed and are ready anytime the
volcano erupts.
</P>
<P>
Residents within the volcano's 10-kilometer buffer zone are
wary of a sudden blast, but they have all been prepared for
evacuation anytime, Bichara said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
