<HEADLINE> Israel's Diamond Industry Recovering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Israel's diamond export totaled
2.02 billion U.S. dollars in the first six months of this year, 6
percent higher than the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
In June alone, diamond exports reached 284 million
U.S. dollars, rising 13.4 percent compared to the same month
last year, according to reports from the Ministry of Industry and
Trade, which were available Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In another sign of the diamond industry's recovery, raw diamond
import totaled 1.823 billion U.S. dollars since January this year,
up 32 percent over the volume of 1.381 billion in the same period
last year, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Ministry officials also said demand for additional workers in
the diamond industry continued rising in June, without giving
exact numbers.
</P>
<P>
While export to the US, Europe and most South East Asian
countries continued to climbing, export to Japan has been on the
decline, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
About 63 percent of Israel's diamond export are to the United
States, 12 percent to Hong Kong, seven percent to Belgium, six
percent to Japan and two percent to Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
