<HEADLINE> New Shanghai Life Sciences Academy Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- A new Shanghai Academy of Life
Sciences that combined eight Shanghai institutes and two Chinese
Academy of Sciences (CAS) research centers held its opening
ceremony today.
</P>
<P>
Xu Zhihong, a vice-president of CAS, said that the academy will
focus on the frontiers of contemporary life science, biological
technology, new pharmaceuticals and modern agricultural technology,
and training young scientists.
</P>
<P>
It will place emphasis on research on paddy rice genes, human
genes, and cell development and decline, he said.
</P>
<P>
The new academy is a combination of the Shanghai Institute of
Biochemistry, Shanghai Institute of Cell Biology, Shanghai
Institute of Materia Medica, Shanghai Institute of Physiology,
Shanghai Brain Research Institute, Shanghai Institute of Plant
Physiology, Shanghai Institute of Entomology, Shanghai
Bioengineering Research Center, Shanghai Research Center of Life
Science, and the State Research Center of Genes, with about 1,900
people.
</P>
<P>
It will give special attention to 650 professionals both inside
and outside the institute and provide them with more funds and
better living conditions. It will also have a guest research staff
of more than 1,000.
</P>
<P>
The academy will increase cooperation between institutes and
CAS, continue coordinating higher education institutes and
research institutes and handle many key state research projects in
hi-tech development and manned space flight, among others.
</P>
</TEXT>
