<HEADLINE> China's Production of Building Materials Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- China's output of building
materials has been on the rise in the first four months this year,
according to latest figures from the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of cement in January-April amounted to 153 million
tons, surging 16.6 percent over the same period last year, and
that of plate glass stood at 55 million weight cases, up 8.0
percent.
</P>
<P>
China has stepped up infrastructure construction in a bid to
stimulate domestic demand. Total investment in the construction
sector in the four months hit 2.5 billion yuan (about 297 million
U.S. dollars), soaring 49.4 percent year on year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
