<HEADLINE> Citizens in Shenzhen Earn More in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- People in the south China city of
Shenzhen continued to enjoy the highest income among the 35 major
Chinese cities, according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Statistics offered by the bureau show that the per capita
monthly income in China's southern boomtown Shenzhen hit 1,523
yuan in March, and the per capita disposable income reached 1,504
yuan while the city's per capita living expenditure stood high at
1,210 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The city was followed by Guangzhou and Shanghai in per capita
monthly income and disposable income. The per capita monthly
income in Guangzhou was 997 yuan and that of Shanghai stood at 880
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The average per capita monthly income of 35 major Chinese
cities stood at 600 yuan, with the per capita monthly disposable
income at 596 yuan and per capita living expenditure at 461 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen adjacent Hong Kong is China's first special economic
zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
