<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Paraguay Beats Japan, Peru Defeats Bolivia at Copa America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Host Paraguay scored its first
win by beating Japan 4-0 while Peru became the first team to sail
into the last eight after edging Bolivia 1-0 on Friday at the Copa
America soccer tournament in Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
Striker Miguel Benitez netted from outside the area to open
scoring for Paraguay and claimed a second midway through the
second half.
</P>
<P>
Roque Santa Cruz, 17, scored the other two for Paraguay, both
from headers.
</P>
<P>
In the other match, twenty-two-year-old Israel Zunica came on
in the 85th minute against Bolivia to score the only goal of the
game.
</P>
<P>
He missed a chance for another goal and was then sent off, all
happening within a span of five minutes.
</P>
<P>
Peru led the group A standings with six points, followed by
Paraguay at four and Bolivia at one. Winless Japan was at the
bottom. 
</P>
</TEXT>
