<HEADLINE> China's Total Investment Up in Jan-April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Total investment in China in the
first four months this year hit 327 billion yuan (about 40 billion
U.S.dollars), surging 18 percent year on year, according to the
National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 190 billion yuan (about 23 billion U.S. dollars)
went to capital construction projects, soaring 22 percent, and 55
billion yuan (about 6.6 billion U.S. dollars) was made for
technical upgrading and transformation, up 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
The aggregate investment in scientific research and poly-
technical services from January to April reached 1.06 billion yuan
(about 127 million U.S. dollars), an increase of 18.7 percent on
an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Investment in education, culture, health care, broadcasting and
social welfare amounted to 12.6 billion yuan (about 1.5 billion U.
S. dollars), soaring 31 percent on a year-on-year basis.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has put the development of science and
education high on the agenda in an effort to accelerate the
country's modernization process.
</P>
<P>
In terms of regions, Guangdong Province, the economic
powerhouse in south China, had the largest amount of investment of
47.8 billion yuan (about 5.8 billion U.S. dollars). Northwest
China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region enjoyed the fastest increase
among all provinces and autonomous regions, with its investment
rocketing 58 percent to 804 million yuan (about 97 million U.S.
dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
