<HEADLINE> Guangdong's Industrial Output Value Leads China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province, the economic
powerhouse in south China, led the country in terms of industrial
output value in the first four months this year, according to the
National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures offered by the bureau show that Guangdong's
industrial output value in the January-April period stood at 289
billion yuan (about 35 billion U.S. dollars), surging 14 percent
on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong was followed by east China's Jiangsu Province, with
an industrial output value of 247 billion yuan, and Shanghai
Municipality with 173 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
A close neighbor of Hong Kong region, Guangdong is the first
province in the country that opened up to the outside world. The
province has developed a high level of processing industry and a
large proportion of its enterprises are export-oriented.  
</P>
</TEXT>
