<HEADLINE> Growth of Telecommunications Industry Slowing Down in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, July 3 (Xinhua) -- China's fast-growing
telecommunications industry has slowed down in growth in the first
four months this year, according to the National Bureau of
Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of program-controlled switchboards surged 38.4
percent year-on-year to 11.9 million lines between January and
April, the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
However, production of optical communications equipment dropped
by 6.5 percent on an annual basis to 4,830 units, and that of
carrier communications equipment dipped 4.4 percent to 1,985 units.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the country produced 8.3 million sets of
mobile communications equipment during the period, soaring 51
percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Production of computers during the time enjoyed a 170 percent
increase to a total of 726 units while that of micro-computers
surged 55.5 percent to 1.03 million.
</P>
<P>
Computer manufacturers in China have enjoyed a rapid growth
these years, and recent surveys show that more and more Chinese
are planning to buy their own personal computers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
