<HEADLINE> China's Output of Electrical Appliances Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The production of household
electrical appliances grew steadily in China in the first four
months this year, according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of color TV sets from January to April hit 13.9
million units, soaring 40.1 percent over the same period last year,
and that of household refrigerators hit 3.7 million units, surging
17.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures offered by the bureau show that the country
produced 4.5 million air conditioners during the period, jumping
up 66.3 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the output of washing machines went up 2.9
percent to 4.6 million units.
</P>
<P>
China has taken measures to stimulate domestic demand in a bid
to minimize the impact of the lingering Asian financial crisis.
Its anti-smuggling drive has also promoted sales of China-made
household electrical appliances, according to market sources.
</P>
<P>
There is also a great potential in the vast rural market where
80 percent of China's 1.2 billion people live, they said.
</P>
</TEXT>
