<HEADLINE> China's Output of Major Chemicals Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- China's chemical industry has
maintained its growing momentum with the output of most major
products keeping on rise in the first four months this year,
according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The production of chemical fertilizers from January to April
increased by 15 percent on an annual basis to 10.4 million tons,
and that of chemical pesticides surged 15.6 percent to 239,200
tons.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, 1.8 million tons of chemical fiber were
produced, surging 16 percent, while 2.6 million tons of plastic
products were turned out, up 12.4 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
The output of ethylene grew 16.2 percent year-on-year to 1.4
million tons and that of plastic resin rose 16.9 percent to 2.6
million tons.
</P>
<P>
Production of caustic soda edged up 1.1 percent to 1.8 million
tons, and that of sulphuric acid surged 13 percent to 7.1 million
tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
