<HEADLINE> China's Steel Production on Steady Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The first four months of this year
witnessed a steady growth of China's steel production with the
output growing 7.3 percent year-on-year to reach 38.95 million
tons, according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of steel products during the period hit 37.26
million tons, surging 15.6 percent on an annual basis, the bureau
said.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, production of pig iron grew by 5.7 percent
over the same period last year to reach 39.45 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The period also saw a year-on-year increase of 10.1 percent in
the output of non-ferrous metals. In the first four months, the
country turned out 2.02 million tons of non-ferrous metals.
</P>
<P>
During the period, the output of aluminium oxide hit 1.21
million tons, up 16.5 percent on an annual basis, and that of
aluminium products hit 438,500 tons, surging 22.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the production of copper products increased
by 19.1 percent over the same period last year to reach 370,800
tons.
</P>
</TEXT>
