<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0730 GMT, July 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA -- The Independent Committee for Election Monitoring (
KIPP) has concluded that there were no systematic deviations in
the June 7 election in Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
"Although there was a lot of problems and violations, there had
been no indication of systematic deceits or political engineering
during the elections," KIPP Secretary General Mulyana W. Kusumah
said.
</P>
<P>
Mulyana said the KIPP regarded the June election as fair and
free and would recognize the final vote count. (Indonesia-
Elections-Deviation)
</P>
