<HEADLINE> Spain, Italy Sail into Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Spain and Italy won their respective
semifinals at Bercy on Friday to sail into the final of the men's
basketball European Championships.
</P>
<P>
Italy blew an 18-point lead but came back to beat two-time
defending champion Yugoslavia 71-62 while Spain defeated host
France 73-60.
</P>
<P>
Forward Gregor Fucka led Italy with 17 points while Dejan
Bodiroga had 17 points and 13 rebounds for Yugoslavia, who had won
four of the last five European titles.
</P>
<P>
