<HEADLINE> Large Gold Mine Operational in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WEIHAI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- A large gold mine went into
operation here Friday in east China's Shandong Province, the
country's leading gold producer.
</P>
<P>
Daye Gold Mine, located in the City of Rushan in east Shandong,
is proved to have 19.6 tons of gold reserves of industrial
development.
</P>
<P>
The open-cut mine, with total investment of 126 million yuan,
will produce 3,000 kg of gold annually when it becomes fully
operational in the near future.
</P>
<P>
Daye Gold Mine is based on a mixed mine which went into
production in 1985, but met with difficulties because of possible
limited gold resources. A group of scientists from the Chinese
Academy of Sciences spent years on studying the local geological
structure and finally discovered a new type of gold deposits there.
</P>
