</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesia does not need a debt relief program as it
is not categorized as a highly-indebted poor country, Coordinating
Minister for Economic, Financial and Industrial Affairs Ginandjar
Kartasasmita said.
</P>
<P>
But rescheduling of Indonesia's foreign debts may be one of the
topics to be discussed at a meeting of the Consultative Group on
Indonesia (CGI) to be held in Paris later this month, Antara News
Agency Saturday quoted Ginandjar as saying. (Indonesia-Debt
Relief)
</P>
