<P>
BRASILIA -- The Brazilian government will provide loans of 500
million reals (about 294 million U.S. dollars) for the
construction of medium-sized hotels in places of tourist
attraction across the country, Minister of Development, Industry
and Trade Celso Lafer said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The loans will be provided by the National Bank for Economic
and Social Development, one of the largest state-owned banks of
the country, with a maturity period of 12 years for the northern,
northeastern and mid-western regions, but only 10 years for other
regions, Lafer said. (Brazil-Tourism)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SAN JOSE -- A Costa Rican delegation led by Foreign Trade
Minister Samuel Guzowski will leave here Sunday for Brussels to
negotiate the quotas of banana exports to the EU market.
</P>
<P>
Guzowski said Friday that is an exploratory trip, and that he
will meet in Brussels with European Commission Vice President Leon
Brittan.
</P>
<P>
He said Costa Rica wants to know the European position on the
Central American bananas exports, after a World Trade Organization
(WTO) decision made it mandatory to change the quota system now in
force. (Costa Rica-EU-Banana Quotas) 
</P>
