<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Attend Trade Fair in South Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar will participate in an
international trade fair beginning from October 19, 1999 in
Johannesburg, South Africa#, to display its wide range of
products.
</P>
<P>
It was disclosed by First Secretary of the Myanmar State Peace
and Development Council Lieutenant General Khin Nyunt at a
commercial affairs meeting here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt said that he saw the potentials of trade between
Myanmar and South Africa while attending the inauguration ceremony
of newly-elected President of South Africa Thabo Mbeki last month.
</P>
<P>
He believes that Myanmar has many products which will be
popular in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
He said Myanmar's participation in this trade fair will benefit
both nations by helping promote the development of bilateral trade
and economy.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar ministries and national entrepreneurs will display and
sell their goods at the fair.
</P>
<P>
It is the second time for Myanmar to take part in the trade
fair held in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Myanmar will hold an international trade fair here
in September this year and another one in Bangkok, Thailand to
promote bilateral trade.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Myanmar's foreign trade
amounted to 3.96 billion U.S. dollars in 1998, up 31 percent over
the previous year. 
</P>
