<HEADLINE> Greene Beaten in 100 Meters at Lausanne Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Newly-crowned world record holder
Maurice Greene was beaten to the second by Ato Boldon of Trinidad
and Tobago in the men's 100 meters sprint at the Athletissima
athletics meeting in Lausanne, Switzerland on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Boldon clocked 9.86 seconds to beat American Greene, who
finished in 9.93. Jason Gardener of Britain was third in 9.98,
edging Namibia's double Olympic silver medalist Frankie Fredericks.
</P>
<P>
In men's 400 meters, Michael Johnson showed no sign of the
thigh injury that prevented him from racing Greene in the U.S.
championships last.
</P>
<P>
The American won in 43.92 seconds, followed by compatriot
Jerome Young in 44.34. Briton Mark Richardson came in third in 44.
53.
</P>
<P>
Marion Jones of the United States clocked the season's best
time for women's 100 meters in 10.80 seconds, 0.11 seconds ahead
of second-placed Sevatheda Fynes of the Bahamas.
</P>
<P>
Another American Inger Miller won the bronze in 11.02.
</P>
<P>
Britain's world record holder Jonathan Edwards took the men's
triple jump title in 17.34 meters.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Denis Kapusti won the silver with 17.31 meters,
followed by third-placed Cuban Yoelbi Quesada at 17.24. 
</P>
