<HEADLINE> 9th Ibero-American Education Conference Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The 9th Ibero-American Education
Conference ended here Friday with a call to raise teaching quality
and offer education for everybody.
</P>
<P>
Education ministers and representatives of 20 countries
attended the two-day meeting and approved the Declaration of
Havana.
</P>
<P>
The document urged the Ibero-American countries to set
deadlines for the eradication of illiteracy, pointing out for the
first time that to promote education is a responsibility of every
nation.
</P>
<P>
It also called for increased education in Spanish and
Portuguese, the two official languages of the Ibero-American
community.
</P>
<P>
The conference is the fourth of a series of 12 meetings before
the regional summit scheduled to open next November, whose central
motto will be "Ibero-America before the serious perils of a
globalized economic crisis." 
