<HEADLINE> Mexico Intensifies Fight Against Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican government has
destroyed a large amount of drugs confiscated recently, official
sources said Friday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 174 tons of marihuana, 689 kilograms of cocaine, 76
kilograms of opium gum, 45 kilograms of heroin and more than 155,
000 units of other substances were incinerated in the last week of
June on the International Day of War Against the Abuse and Illicit
Traffic of Drugs.
</P>
<P>
Metamphetamines, psychotropic pills, marihuana plants and seeds,
and opium poppy seeds were also among the items incinerated, said
the Federal Attorney General Office.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Attorney General Office reaffirmed its permanent
commitment to combating drug trafficking "in whatever of its
aspects." 
</P>
