<HEADLINE> Murderer of 8 Girls Sentenced to Death in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- A man who murdered eight girls in
Beijing was sentenced to death Friday by the Beijing N0. 1
Intermediate People's Court.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Lianrong, 37, a resident of west Beijing's Shijingshan
District, was found guilty of killing eight girls, aged between 18
and 24, on the early morning of May 30.
</P>
<P>
This is the worst homicide case in the Chinese capital in the
past 50 years, and aroused great public concern.
</P>
<P>
The eight women, all salesgirls at the Fujian Jindeli
Handicraft Co. Ltd, lived in a rented flat next to Zhao's in an
apartment building in N0. 23 compound on the Shijingshan Road.
</P>
<P>
Zhao, a worker of a Beijing machine tools plant, broke into the
girls' flat, searching for money and valuables at about three o'
clock on the early morning of May 30.
</P>
<P>
He stabbed the eight girls in the neck and chest more than 110
times and fled after failing to find money and valuables.
</P>
<P>
Zhao was arrested on the early morning of June 6 by the Beijing
police and was indicted on June 21 by the N0. 1 Branch of the
Beijing People's Procuratorate on homicide charges.
</P>
<P>
The court heard the interrogations Friday, carried out the
cross-examination and listened to the final statements of the
prosecutors and the defence lawyer.
</P>
<P>
Zhao committed murder, the court decided and thus reached the
verdict according to the Criminal Law of the People's Republic of
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
