said Friday he opted for the Turin side instead.
</P>
<P>
Oliseh spent one season in Italy, at Reggiana, several years
ago but failed to make his mark. After two years at FC Koln in
Germany, he was snapped up as a bargain by Ajax, eager to replace
star midfield dynamos like Clarence Seedorf, sold to Real Madrid,
and Edgar Davids, who will be one of his new team-mates at Juve.
</P>
<P>
Throughout the '90s he has been a fixture in the highly-skilled
but erratic Nigeria team that shone but ultimately failed to
fulfill its extravagant promise at last year's World Cup.
</P>
<P>
Juventus did not disclose the terms of the contract that will
keep Oliseh in Turin until 2004. 
