<HEADLINE> Argentine Stock Index Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The leading Merval index of
the Buenos Aires Stock exchange closed up by 2.19 percent at 523.
98 points on Friday against 512.71 on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 36.856 million dollars against 42.087 million
dollars on the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The annual interbank rate of interest reduced to 6.6 percent in
the 24-hour term. The peso parity against the dollar remained
unchanged at 0.997 for purchase and 1.002 for sale. 
</P>
