<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Slightly Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchanges on
Friday closed slightly up with the benchmark IPC index surging by
33.01 points, or 0.56 percent, at 5,887.61 points.
</P>
<P>
Operators exchanged 78.878 million shares for an amount of some
135.982 million dollars against 140.052 million shares worth 264.
038 million dollars on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, the peso, stood at 9.55 to one dollar for
sale and 9.20 for purchase in the main exchange houses of the
Mexico City, compared with 9.50 for sale and 9.20 for purchase on
Thursday. 
